com.embeddedunveiled.serial.datalogger

Class SerialComToFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.embeddedunveiled.serial.datalogger.SerialComToFile

  • public final class SerialComToFile
extends java.lang.Object

    Reads data from serial port and send it to given file. Provides different ways to read data from serial port. Logging can be started/stopped now or can be scheduled for future runs.

    Author:
    Rishi Gupta

    • Method Detail

      • startLogging

        public boolean startLogging(SerialComManager scm,
                   long comPortHandle,
                   int readingStyle,
                   int pollingFrequency,
                   java.io.File logFile,
                   ISerialComToFileErrListener errListener)
                     throws java.io.FileNotFoundException

        Starts logging data from given serial port to given file. If readingStyle is NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC, a Java thread polls serial port for data with periodic interval given by pollingFrequency. If readingStyle is BLOCKING, a Java thread will read data from serial blocking until data is available. Once data is read it will loop back and may block again until data is available. If readingStyle is DATALISTENER, a data listener will be registered. Whenever data is available at serial port it will be read and native thread will call a Java method passing data read.

        Parameters:
        scm - instance of SerialComManager class with which this serial port was opened.
        comPortHandle - handle of the opened serial port from which to read data.
        readingStyle - specifies how data should be read from serial port. It must be set to one of the following constants; NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC, BLOCKING or DATALISTENER.
        pollingFrequency - specifies frequency of poll (in milliseconds) if readingStyle is NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC. For other reading styles it will be ignored.
        logFile - file in which data read from serial port will be saved.
        errListener - object that will listen for error exceptions while logging.
        Returns:
        true on success.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if log file is not found.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if readingStyle is not one of the following constants; NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC, BLOCKING or DATALISTENER. If given log file is not a file.

      • scheduleLaterLogging

        public boolean scheduleLaterLogging(java.lang.String logStartTime,
                           java.lang.String logStopTime,
                           SerialComManager scm,
                           long comPortHandle,
                           int readingStyle,
                           int pollingFrequency,
                           java.io.File logFile,
                           ISerialComToFileErrListener errListener)
                             throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                                    java.text.ParseException

        Starts logging data from given serial port to given file. If readingStyle is NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC, a Java thread polls serial port for data with periodic interval given by pollingFrequency. If readingStyle is BLOCKING, a Java thread will read data from serial blocking until data is available. Once data is read it will loop back and may block again until data is available. If readingStyle is DATALISTENER, a data listener will be registered. Whenever data is available at serial port it will be read and native thread will call a Java method passing data read.

        If the argument logStartTime is null, logging will start as soon as this method is called. Application must specify future time which will be used to automatically stop the logging. However, application can stop the logging at any point of time by calling unscheduleOrStopLaterLogging() methid.

        Parameters:
        logStartTime - string ("dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm:ss") specifying time when to start logging or null if logging should start as soon as this method is called.
        logStopTime - string ("dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm:ss") specifying time when to stop logging in future.
        scm - instance of SerialComManager class with which this serial port was opened.
        comPortHandle - handle of the opened serial port from which to read data.
        readingStyle - specifies how data should be read from serial port. It must be set to one of the following constants; NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC, BLOCKING or DATALISTENER.
        pollingFrequency - specifies frequency of poll (in milliseconds) if readingStyle is NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC. For other reading styles it will be ignored.
        logFile - file in which data read from serial port will be saved.
        errListener - object that will listen for error exceptions while logging.
        Returns:
        true on success.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if log file is not found.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if readingStyle is not one of the following constants; NONBLOCKING_PERIODIC, BLOCKING or DATALISTENER. If given log file is not a file.
        java.text.ParseException - if the given start or stop time string is in incorrect format.
